section.section:
In this section and in § 10-108.4 of this subtitle, "financial institution" means:
a depository institution, as defined in the Federal Deposit Insurance Act at 12 U.S.C. § 1813(c);
a federal or state credit union, as defined in the Federal Credit Union Act at 12 U.S.C. § 1752;
a State credit union regulated under Title 6 of the Financial Institutions Article; or
a benefit association, insurance company, safe deposit company, money market mutual fund, or similar entity doing business in the State that holds property or maintains accounts reflecting property belonging to others.

The notice shall contain the following information, to the extent known by the Administration:
the address of the Administration;
the telephone number, address, and name of a contact person at the Administration;
the name and Social Security number or other taxpayer identification number of the obligor;
the address of the obligor;
for each account of the obligor, the obligor's account number and known balance with the financial institution;
the amount of arrearage that the financial institution shall seize and attach from one or more of the accounts of the obligor; and
a statement instructing the financial institution to immediately attach and seize the amount of arrearage stated in item (vi) of this paragraph from one or more of the accounts of the obligor and, upon subsequent notice by the Administration, to forward the amount to the Administration.

The notice shall contain the following information, to the extent known by the Administration:
the address of the Administration;
the telephone number, address, and name of a contact person at the Administration;
the name and Social Security number or other taxpayer identification number of the obligor;
the address of the obligor;
for each account of the obligor, the obligor's account number and known balances with the financial institution;
the total amount of the arrearage owed by the obligor;
the date the notice is being sent;
a statement informing the obligor that the Administration has directed the financial institution to seize and attach the amount of the arrearage owed by the obligor from one or more of the accounts of the obligor and, upon subsequent notice by the Administration, to forward the amount to the Administration; and
a statement informing the obligor that, unless a timely challenge is made to the Administration by the obligor or an account holder of interest under subsection (h) of this section, the Administration shall notify the financial institution to forward the amount seized and attached by the financial institution to the Administration.

A challenge under paragraph (1)(i) of this subsection shall:
be in writing;
be received by the Administration within 30 days from the date of the notice under subsection (e) of this section;
be sent to the contact person identified in the notice sent to the obligor under subsection (e) of this section; and
specify, in detail, the reasons for the challenge.

The Administration shall release or reduce the amount seized and attached by the financial institution for a mistake of fact, including:
a mistake in the identity of the obligor;
a mistake in the ownership of an account;
a mistake in the contents of an account;
a mistake in the amount of arrearage due; or
any other good cause.
